content:
Set Up an Incident Presence Status

To let support agents assigned to the Incident channel mark themselves as available to resolve incidents:

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS:
CUSTOMIZE APPLICATION
MANAGE PROFILES AND PERMISSION SETS
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
Available in: Lightning Experience with your standard Service Cloud license
Available in: Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

In Setup, from the Quick Find box, enter Presence Statuses, and then select Presence Statuses.
Click New.
Enter a status name and developer name.
Set the status to Online to let agents receive new incident work.
Select Incident as the channel.
Save your changes.

Give users access to the Omni-Channel presence status.

In Setup, from the Quick Find box, enter Permission Sets, and then select Permission Sets.
Click New.
Enter a label and an API name.
Save your changes.
Under the permission setâ€™s Apps section, select Service Presence Statuses Access.
Click Edit.
Add the Incident presence status and save.
Select Manage Assignments.
Click Add Assignments and add users with the Service Cloud User license. Click Assign.
Save your changes.
title: Setting Up Incident Presence Status in Service Cloud
